The HCP model of b-cell cluster
In this study we introduced the HCP lattice to simulate b-cell
clusters. In figure 9 we lay out the HCP structure in contrast to the
SCP lattice that is conventionally used. In 2D HCP nc = 6, a value
1.5 fold higher than in SCP. The difference is more significant in the
real 3D situation, with nc = 12 in HCP, 2 fold higher than in SCP.
The number of cells in a 2D regular HCP cluster with edge size n is
given by NHCP(n) = 3n223n+1, and in a 3D HCP it is given by:

